AttributeValuesData.AttributeValue: Gray or gray-brown and can be mistaken for Acer rubrum

Silver Maple is one of the first trees to flower in the spring, often just after the snow has melted and well before leaves appear. This tree is often planted as a shade tree because it is a fast-growing species, but that comes with a cost. Silver Maple is brittle and limbs are easily broken in storms, and the shallow roots can lift up sidewalks and driveways. Other names for the Silver Maple include White Maple, Soft Maple, and River Maple.
Reddish turning greenish yellow, predominantly staminate or pistillate, dense clusters similar to Red Maple
1 1/2- 3" long paired samaras, broad wings spread at a 90 degree angle. The largest of all maple samaras
Opposite, simple 5-7" long and nearly as wide, 5 deeply divided, pointed lobes; coarsely toothed margins, green above, silver-white beneath. Twig has unpleasant smell when bruised or broken.
massive, spreading limbs, shaggy bark, and deeply lobed leaves.
